			<p>Integrated react Single Page App with PHP Multi Page App</p>
			<p>
				The main Exotel dashboard is developed using PHP and jQuery, as
				several new upcoming projects required sophisticated UI and fast
				iteration. The deadlines didn't allow for micro-frontend
				architecture modal to be implemented.
			</p>
			<p>
				I implemented <a href="#LCD">Live Call Dashboard</a> in react as
				an SPA and integrated it with PHP backend so that the pages
				developed in PHP and jQuery continue to function as before and
				the pages developed in React can be accessed on new routes.
			</p>
			<p class="pagebreak">
				I wrote, maintained, owned, documented and mentored others for:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					CD pipeline for deploying PHP and React projects together
					using jenkins AWS-s3 and AWS-EC2
				</li>
				<li>
					Integration code to load react bundle on relevant routes
					only
				</li>
				<li>
					CSS scoping so the old and new styling don't conflict with
					each other
				</li>
				<li>
					APIs to pass data between server side PHP and client side
					React
					<ul>
						<li>
							data to be present during page load injected into JS
							while PHP is forming the response
						</li>
						<li>
							non critical data could be requested by react
							through API calls
						</li>
					</ul>
				</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				This made future UI development faster and fixed some of the
				performance issues that old pages faced. Newer pages were
				available quickly as the UI was loaded with minimal data and
				further data could be fetched parallelly or when needed reducing
				server cost and page load times.
			</p>

